4. 

# Partition (Training Dataset : Test Dataset = 7:3)
y      <- UB$Personal.Loan                            # Target
 
set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = T)   # Index  7:3 
UB.trd <- UB[ind$Resample1,]                          # Training Dataset
UB.ted <- UB[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Dataset

5.

Package "caret" API R . Package "caret" (Grid Search), (Random Search), . cp (Complexity Parameter) , . .

fitControl <- trainControl(method = "cv", number = 5,  # 5-Fold Cross Validation (5-Fold CV)
                           allowParallel = TRUE)       #  

set.seed(100)                                          # For CV
rtree.caret <- train(x = UB.trd[,-9],                  # Training Dataset including Only  
                     y = UB.trd[,"Personal.Loan"],     # Training Dataset including Only Target
                     method = "rpart", 
                     trControl = fitControl)

Caution! Package "caret" rpart() xval = 0, cp . , Package "caret" "rpart" , train(Target ~ , data) One-hot Encoding . One-hot Encoding train(x = , y = Target ) .

1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

rtree.roc  <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "gray")         # roc( class,  )
auc        <- round(auc(rtree.roc), 3)
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")

Caution! Package "pROC" ROC .

#  plot.roc() 
plot.roc(rtree.roc,   
         col="gray",                                      # Line Color
         print.auc = TRUE,                                # AUC  
         print.auc.col = "red",                           # AUC  
         print.thres = TRUE,                              # Cutoff Value  
         print.thres.pch = 19,                            # Cutoff Value   
         print.thres.col = "red",                         # Cutoff Value   
         auc.polygon = TRUE,                              #     
         auc.polygon.col = "gray90")                      #    

#  ggroc() 
ggroc(rtree.roc) +
annotate(geom = "text", x = 0.9, y = 1.0,
label = paste("AUC = ", auc),
size = 5,
color="red") +
theme_bw()

2) Package Epi

pacman::p_load("Epi")       
# install_version("etm", version = "1.1", repos = "http://cran.us.r-project.org")

ROC(pp, ac, plot = "ROC")                                 # ROC( ,  class)

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

rtree.pred <- prediction(pp, ac)                          # prediction( ,  class)  

rtree.perf <- performance(rtree.pred, "tpr", "fpr")       # performance(, "", "1-")                      
plot(rtree.perf, col = "gray")                            # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(rtree.pred, "auc")              # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")
